      • checkParameter

        protected String checkParameter(String parameter)
        It seems that JConsole inserts "String" as value of an argument to an operation by default. This method is to convert this to null also it converts "" or blanks to null
        Parameters:
        parameter - a String parameter
        Returns:
        null if initial parameter is 'String', "" or blanks

      • getPackageName

        protected String getPackageName(String configurationPackageName)
        This is only a place holder for getting the package name and remove JConsole 'String'. We don't check the package name here for this see ConfigurationObjectFactory NOTE do not call Package.getPackages() to check package name as it will return the list of known package to the caller's class loader. Once a class instance belonging to a new package is created this list is updated with the new package name but not before.
        Parameters:
        configurationPackageName - configuration package name
        Returns:
        null if initial parameter is 'String', "" or blanks

      • handleChangeInChildrenOfType

        protected void handleChangeInChildrenOfType(RegistrationType type,
                                            Name parentName)
        Handles a change in the set of children of the given type under the configuration node represented by this MBean.
        Parameters:
        type - a configuration node type
        parentName - name of the common parent to all the children impacted by the change. This is either this configuration node's path itself, or the path of one of its container children
